n > 1
\frac{1}{2} (1) (1+1) = 1
N = k
1 + 2 + 3 + ... + k = \frac{1}{2} k(k+1)
N = k + 1
1 + 2 + 3 + ... + k + (k + 1)
\frac{1}{2} k (k + 1) + (k + 1)
\frac{1}{2} (k+1) (k+1+1)
\frac{1}{2} (k+1) (k+2)
\frac{1}{2}K\color{red}{(K+1)}+\color{red}{(K+1)}\;\;\;\:(**)
(**)\;\;\;=\color{red}{(K+1)}\left(\frac{1}{2}K+1\right)=\color{red}{(K+1)}\left(\frac{K+2}{2}\right)=\frac{1}{2}(K+1)(K+2)
n=1
